<TITLE> Child protection alliance launched </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, October 17 (bdnews24.com) - The Child Protection Movement (Shishu Shurokkha Andolon), an alliance of over 135 children organisations, was launched on Friday, to mark 'National Child Rights Week'. The occasion was observed by Save the Children Sweden  Denmark (SCSD) and associate organisations at Ramna Park in the capital, with a cultural programme and children's 'fun fair'. Artist Mustafa Monowar formally inaugurated a children's rally 10:30 am. Niels Bentzen Pedersen, SCSD country representative, deputy country director Obaidur Rahman, were among those present. About 40 children's clubs of 21 organisations linked to SCSD, along with independent children's organisations, including Eachchey Media, Child Brigade, Bhorer Alo, NCTF, BILLS, AUPORAJEO Bangladesh, are united under the Shishu Shurokkha Andolon. To assure health, education and safety of all children and to spread awareness theirs needs and rights, the newly formed alliance will embark on a systematic movement to achieve their common universal goals. b
